The paper discusses semi-supervised learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on consistency regularization, which is a technique used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses image datasets (CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100) and discusses techniques for improving convergence during training, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes modifications to the training procedure, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the consistency loss on the model's predictions, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
